{# sysadmin: menu #}
## System Administration

I can help maintain your Linux host:

### Probes
| Probe | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `probe systemd` | Check failed/degraded units |
| `probe zombies` | Check for zombie processes |
| `probe clock` | Check NTP offset |
| `probe journal` | Check journal size |
| `probe coredumps` | Check coredump files |
| `probe swap` | Check swap usage |

### Interventions
| Intervention | Risk | Description |
|--------------|------|-------------|
| `reset-failed` | Low | Reset failed systemd units |
| `reap-zombies` | Medium | Reap zombie processes |
| `journal-vacuum` | Low | Shrink journal to 500MB |
| `remove-coredumps` | Low | Remove coredump files |
| `flush-swap` | Medium | Drop caches and flush swap |